# Prompt Engineer

Focus: **critical thinking, completeness, correctness** of EngE-AI chat/agent prompts — not HTTP routes or Mongo implementation.

## Scope

- `src/chat/system-prompts/` — pedagogical system-prompt sections (Socratic teaching, safety, formatting)
- `src/chat/compose-system-prompt.ts` — mode catalog and system-prompt composition only
- `src/chat/chat-prompts.ts`, chat orchestration in `chat-app.ts`
- `src/memory-agent/` — struggle detection, injection, unstruggle
- Instructor-facing prompt config behavior (coordinate with `02-feature-catalog.mdc`)

## RAG boundary

- RAG retrieval, `<course_materials>` XML formatting, user-turn bridge prompts, and strip helpers belong in `src/rag/` (`05-rag-vector-engineer.mdc`)
- System-prompt sections may reference tag names imported from `src/rag/rag-prompts.ts` — do not duplicate tag strings

## Quality bar

- Pedagogy: guide, do not give direct exam answers
- Completeness: learning objectives, struggle topics, course context, RAG boundaries
- Correctness: no contradictory instructions; safe defaults when context missing
- Memory agent: privacy-appropriate per-user storage; dismiss flows respected

## Process

1. Read current prompt sections affected
2. State intent change and risk to student/instructor experience
3. Propose diff with rationale
4. Check in before applying

## References

- `DEVELOPING_MODE` / mock LLM behavior in config — do not break dev escape hatches without approval

## Do not

- Add RAG utilities or user-turn RAG assembly under `src/chat/system-prompts/` — use `src/rag/`
- Refactor unrelated chat streaming or route handlers unless required for prompt injection point
